quest_title: Let \(z _ { 1 } , z _ { 2 }\) be two complex numbers such that \(z _ { 1 } + z _ { 2 }\) and \(z _ { 1 } z _ { 2 }\) both are real, then
explanation_txt:
Let \(z _ { 1 } = a + i b , z _ { 2 } = c + i d\), then

\(z _ { 1 } + z _ { 2 }\) is real \(\Rightarrow ( a + c ) + i ( b + d )\) is real

\(\Rightarrow b + d = 0 \quad \Rightarrow d = - b \quad \dots (i) \)

\(z _ { 1 } z _ { 2 }\) is real \(\Rightarrow ( a d - b d ) + i ( a c + b c )\) is real

\(\Rightarrow a d + b c = 0 \Rightarrow a ( - b ) + b c = 0 \Rightarrow a = c\)

\(\therefore z _ { 1 } = a + i b = c - i d = \overline { z } _ { 2 } \quad ( \because a = c \text { and } b = - d ) \)

quest_title: A car travels 6 km at an angle 45\(\mathrm{{}^\circ}\) east of north then travel a distance of 4 km an angle of 45\(\mathrm{{}^\circ}\) west of north. The displacement of car is
explanation_txt:
\(\begin{aligned} \mathrm{d}_{\mathrm{x}} &=\mathrm{d}_{1} \sin 45^{0} \hat{\mathrm{i}}+\mathrm{d}_{2} \sin 45^{0}(-\hat{\mathrm{i}}) \\ &=\sqrt{2} \mathrm{i} \end{aligned}\)

\(\begin{aligned} \mathrm{d}_{\mathrm{y}} &=\mathrm{d}_{1} \cos 45^{0} \hat{\mathrm{j}}+\mathrm{d}_{2} \cos 45^{0} \hat{\mathrm{j}} \\ &=5 \sqrt{2} \hat{\mathrm{j}} \end{aligned}\)

\(\begin{aligned} \therefore \quad \mathrm{d} &=\sqrt{\mathrm{d}_{\mathrm{x}}^{2}+\mathrm{d}_{\mathrm{y}}^{2}} \\ &=\sqrt{(\sqrt{2})^{2}+(5 \sqrt{2})^{2}} \\ &=2 \sqrt{13} \mathrm{km} \end{aligned}\)
